race.comment: MISS LYRA (5) is fourth up and should be ready to show more. Comes back 200m and will find this more suitable than the 1000 Guineas at Hobart. Keeps the top hoop and her best is good enough. LAST TREMBLE (8) raced forward and just missed here this grade over a mile. Has a low gate and a handy 2kg and coming back to 1400m shouldn't bother. Will get every chance to go one better. THEM'S THE BREAKS (6) peaks and is busting to win. Draws awkwardly again but has Luke Currie aboard today, replacing the 2kg apprentice. She should be right in it again. THE PIRATE QUEEN (9) spiked her figures beaten 1.2L this track/trip at big odds. Came hard from back in the field and has the inside gate today and handy 2kg claim. Deserves consideration on the back of that run.
